[[File:IAC2014londeixaltonperry.jpg|thumb|Pauline Londeix with Gregg Alton and Gregg Perry, at the International AIDS conference 2014 in Melbourne]] '''Pauline Londeix''' (born in 1986) is a French activist<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.lesinrocks.com/2011/09/29/actualite/acces-aux-generiques-loperation-coup-de-poing-dact-up-chez-novartis-118938/|title=Accès aux génériques: l'opération coup de poing d'Act-Up chez Novartis|work=Les Inrocks|access-date=2018-02-05|language=fr-FR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://yagg.com/2012/12/01/les-associations-passent-elles-a-cote-dune-question-cruciale-le-cout-et-la-perennite-des-soins-par-pauline-londeix/|title="Les associations passent-elles à côté d’une question cruciale: le coût et la pérennité des soins?" par Pauline Londeix|date=2012-12-01|work=Yagg|access-date=2018-02-06|language=fr-FR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.seronet.info/article/le-probleme-du-prix-des-medicaments-dans-notre-societe-est-systemique-22-68728|title="Le problème du prix des médicaments dans notre société est systémique" (2/2) {{!}} Seronet|website=www.seronet.info|language=fr|access-date=2018-02-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aidsalliance.org/assets/000/001/007/INSIGHT3_PaulineLondeix_original.pdf?1412944365|title=Supply and demand: Why drug prices and rade barriers are blocking drug access and what activists can do about it|last=|first=|date=|website=aidsalliance.org|archive-url=|archive-date=February 6, 2018|dead-url=|access-date=February 6, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mediapart.fr/journal/international/090212/sommet-europe-inde-le-risque-est-dentraver-la-production-indienne-de-me|title=|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> researcher and writer,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.laltiplano.fr/foreignrights/thelesbianmanifesto.php|title=Foreign rights L'Altiplano : The Lesbian Manifesto|website=www.laltiplano.fr|access-date=2018-02-05}}</ref> who has been particularly involved in the fight for the access to generic medicines used against [[HIV]] <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mediapart.fr/journal/international/090212/sommet-europe-inde-le-risque-est-dentraver-la-production-indienne-de-me|title=|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> and [[Hepatitis C virus|Hepatitis C virus (HCV)]], in particular through contributing to challenging monopolies and intellectual property barriers in the Global South, but also in high income countries, such as France. In 2008, she was the Vice President of the French [[HIV]]/[[AIDS]] organisation [[ACT UP|Act Up-Paris]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.rfi.fr/emission/20170829-act-up-aujourd-hui-vih-sida-association|title=Priorité santé - Act-up aujourd’hui|date=2017-08-29|work=RFI|access-date=2018-02-06|language=fr-FR}}</ref><ref>Vice-President (2008) http://www.regards.fr/acces-payant/archives-web/une-nouvelle-equipe-pour-act-up,3086</ref> In 2011, she co-founded [[Act Up-Basel]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vacarme.org/article2260.html|title=Quand les malades investissent les rues de Bâle&nbsp;— Vacarme|website=www.vacarme.org}}</ref>
== Background == She has been involved in the fight against HIV/AIDS since 2005. In 2009, she took part to a cross interview with [[Françoise Barré-Sinoussi]] in the French daily paper [[Libération]][[.http://www.liberation.fr/terre/2009/11/06/avec-moins-de-1-de-l-argent-investi-pour-sauver-les-banques-il-n-y-aurait-aucun-souci_592129|.]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.liberation.fr/terre/2009/11/06/avec-moins-de-1-de-l-argent-investi-pour-sauver-les-banques-il-n-y-aurait-aucun-souci_592129|title="Avec moins de 1 % de l’argent investi pour sauver les banques, il n’y aurait aucun souci"|work=Libération.fr|access-date=2018-02-05|language=fr}}</ref> Since 2011, she has been particularly involved in the access to new [[hepatitis C]] breakthrough treatments : the direct acting antivirals. She is the main author <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/sarah-boseley-global-health/2014/mar/17/hepatitis-c-pharmaceuticals-industry|title=New hepatitis C drugs must be affordable worldwide, say campaigners|first=Sarah|last=Boseley|date=17 March 2014|website=the Guardian}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mediapart.fr/journal/france/200416/hepatite-c-peut-soigner-n-importe-quel-prix|title=|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.twn.my/title2/intellectual_property/info.service/2014/ip140309.htm|title=|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> of the [[Doctors of the World|Medecins du Monde]]'s report "New treatments for hepatitis C virus : strategies for achieving universal access" (2014) <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.lemonde.fr/sciences/article/2014/03/17/inegalites-face-a-l-hepatite-c_4384588_1650684.html|title=|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.lemonde.fr/planete/article/2015/01/22/hepatite-c-bataille-pour-l-acces-a-un-traitement-revolutionnaire_4561824_3244.html|title=|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> that was presented during the [[International AIDS Conference|International aids conference]] that took place in Melbourne.<ref>{{Citation|last=International AIDS Conference|title=HCV drug pricing|date=2014-07-28|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6LXF19d235M|accessdate=2018-02-05}}</ref> She is the author or the co-author of various articles and reports linked to access to medicines.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aidsalliance.org/resources/450-aids-today-2014-edition|title=|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.who.int/bulletin/volumes/93/11/15-157784/en/|title=Access to hepatitis C medicines|website=World Health Organization|language=en-GB|access-date=2018-02-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.unsgaccessmeds.org/inbox/2016/3/4/pauline-londeix-enligsh-translation|title=Pauline Londeix, ACCESS (English Translation)|work=High-Level Panel on Access to Medicines|access-date=2018-02-05|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Ford|first=Nathan|last2=Wiktor|first2=Stefan|last3=Kaplan|first3=Karyn|last4=Andrieux-Meyer|first4=Isabelle|last5=Hill|first5=Andrew|last6=Radhakrishnan|first6=Priti|last7=Londeix|first7=Pauline|last8=Forette|first8=Chloe|last9=Momenghalibaf|first9=Azzi|date=2015-11-01|title=Ten priorities for expanding access to HCV treatment for people who inject drugs in low- and middle-income countries|url=http://www.ijdp.org/article/S0955-3959(15)00137-1/abstract|journal=International Journal of Drug Policy|language=English|volume=26|issue=11|pages=1088–1093|doi=10.1016/j.drugpo.2015.05.004|issn=0955-3959}}</ref>
