{{Infobox person | name = Shail Upadhya | image = | alt = | caption = | other_names = | occupation = Nepalese fashion designer | birth_date = 9 August 1935 | death_date = 31 January 2013 | birth_place = [[Nepal]] | death_place = [[New York City]] }}
'''Shail Upadhya''' (1935-2013) was a [[Nepal]]ese diplomat, [[United Nations]] [[disarmament]] expert and [[fashion design]]er.
==Career== In a second career, Upadhya worked as a fashion designer, becoming a social fixture in [[New York City]], known for his flamboyant and colorful suits and outfits.<ref name="nypost">{{cite news|url=https://nypost.com/2014/02/22/kin-of-late-fashion-designer-battle-baroness-over-fortune/|title=Kin of late fashion designer battle baroness over fortune &#124; New York Post|publisher=nypost.com|accessdate=2015-02-13|first=Julia|last=Marsh|date=2014-02-22}}</ref> He was a prominent presence in the 2011 documentary film ''[[Bill Cunningham New York]],'' about [[New York Times]] fashion photographer [[Bill Cunningham (American photographer)|Bill Cunningham]].<ref name="forbes">{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/raquellaneri/2011/03/17/shail-upadhya-the-other-star-of-bill-cunninghams-new-york/|title=Shail Upadhya: The Other Star Of 'Bill Cunningham's New York' - Forbes|publisher=forbes.com|accessdate=2015-02-13|first=Raquel|last=Laneri}}</ref> He lived in New York City, [[Southampton, New York]], and [[Miami, Florida]].<ref name="legacy">{{cite web|url=http://www.legacy.com/obituaries/nytimes/obituary.aspx?n=shail-k-upadhya&pid=162792851&fhid=2058|title=SHAIL UPADHYA Obituary - New York, NY &#124; New York Times|publisher=legacy.com|accessdate=2015-02-13}}</ref>
Upadhya was interviewed on ''[[Da Ali G Show]]'' by [[Sacha Baron Cohen]]'s character [[Brüno]] at [[New York Fashion Week]].<ref name="youtube">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=S01PgbnE4VA|title=Bruno Interviews Shail Upadhya - YouTube|publisher=youtube.com|accessdate=2015-09-22}}</ref>
