'''Soumitro Banerjee''' (born 1960) is an Indian electrical engineer and a professor at the Department of Physical Sciences of the [[Indian Institute of Science Education and Research, Kolkata]].<ref name="Faculty profile">{{Cite web |url=http://www.iiserkol.ac.in/people/faculty/dps/soumitro |title=Faculty profile |date=2017 |publisher=Department of Physical Sciences, IISER Kolkata}}</ref> He is known for his studies on bifurcation phenomena in power electronic circuits<ref name="Brief Profile of the Awardee">{{Cite web |url=http://ssbprize.gov.in/Content/Detail.aspx?AID=392 |title=Brief Profile of the Awardee |date=2017 |publisher=Shanti Swarup Bhatnagar Prize}}</ref> and is an elected fellow of all the three major Indian science academies viz. the [[National Academy of Sciences, India]],<ref name="NASI fellows">{{Cite web |url=http://www.nasi.org.in/fellows.asp?RsFilter=B |title=NASI fellows |date=2016 |publisher=National Academy of Sciences, India}}</ref> [[Indian Academy of Sciences]],<ref name="Fellow profile">{{Cite web |url=http://www.ias.ac.in/describe/fellow/Banerjee,_Prof._Soumitro |title=Fellow profile |date=2016 |publisher=Indian Academy of Sciences}}</ref> and [[Indian National Science Academy]].<ref name="Indian fellow">{{Cite web |url=http://insaindia.res.in/detail.php?id=P08-1455 |title=Indian fellow |date=2016 |publisher=Indian National Science Academy}}</ref> He is also a fellow of [[The World Academy of Sciences]],<ref name="TWAS fellow">{{Cite web |url=http://twas.org/member/banerjee-soumitro |title=TWAS fellow |date=2016 |publisher=The World Academy of Sciences}}</ref> [[Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers]],<ref name="IEEE Fellows Directory">{{Cite web |url=https://www.ieee.org/membership_services/membership/fellows/fellowsDirectory.html# |title=IEEE Fellows Directory |date=2016 |publisher=Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers}}</ref> West Bengal Academy of Sciences and the [[Indian National Academy of Engineering]].<ref name="INAE fellows">{{Cite web |url=https://inae.in/search-of-fellows/ |title=INAE fellows |date=2016 |publisher=Indian National Academy of Engineers }}{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> The [[Council of Scientific and Industrial Research]], the apex agency of the Government of India for scientific research, awarded him the [[Shanti Swarup Bhatnagar Prize for Science and Technology]], one of the highest Indian science awards for his contributions to Engineering Sciences in 2003.<ref name="View Bhatnagar Awardees">{{cite web | url=http://ssbprize.gov.in/Content/AwardeeList.aspx | title=View Bhatnagar Awardees | publisher=Shanti Swarup Bhatnagar Prize | date=2016 | accessdate=November 12, 2016}}</ref>{{Refn|group=note|Long link - please select award year to see details}}

== Biography ==
[[File:IIT Kharagpur Old Building 1951.jpg|thumb|left|235px|The [[Hijli Detention Camp]] (photographed in 1951) served as IIT Kharagpur's first academic building]]
Soumitro Banerjee, born on 17 October 1960 at Kolkata in the Indian state of [[West Bengal]], did his graduate studies at [[Bengal Engineering College]] of the [[University of Calcutta]] from where he earned a BE degree in electrical engineering in 1981 and moved to the [[Indian Institute of Technology, Delhi]] to gain an MTech in Energy Studies in 1983.<ref name="Profile on TWAS">{{Cite web |url=http://twas.org/sites/default/files/member/cv.pdf |title=Profile on TWAS |date=2017 |publisher=The World Academy of Scineces}}</ref> After enrolling for PhD at IIT Delhi, he took up the post of a lecturer at the [[Indian Institute of Technology, Kharagpur]] in 1985 and while serving there he received his doctoral degree in 1988 for his thesis, ''Magnetic Energy Storage Units for Improvement of Power System Stability''. He served IIT Kharagpur till 2009 during which period held the positions of an assistant professor (1990–98), associate professor (1998–2003) and a professor. In 2009, he moved to the [[Indian Institute of Science Education and Research, Kolkata]] where he serves as a professor.<ref name="Soumitro Banerjee on IISER">{{Cite web |url=http://www.iiserkol.ac.in/component/sobipro/?pid=54&sid=135:Soumitro-Banerjee&Itemid=0 |title=Soumitro Banerjee on IISER |date=2017 |publisher=Indian Institute of Science Education and Research, Kolkata |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161206100122/http://www.iiserkol.ac.in/component/sobipro/?pid=54&sid=135:Soumitro-Banerjee&Itemid=0 |archivedate=2016-12-06 |df= }}</ref>

== Legacy ==
[[File:Stick-slip.svg|thumb|235px|An example of Stick-slip]]
Banerjee's researches have been focused on [[nonlinear dynamics]] and [[bifurcation theory]] and his experiments and analyses widened the understanding of border collision bifurcations.<ref name="Brief Profile of the Awardee" /> He worked on hybrid dynamical systems such as switching electronic circuits and mechanical systems showing impacts or [[stick-slip phenomenon]] and demonstrated border-collision bifurcation, a mode of dynamical transition, occurring in those systems.<ref name="Indian fellow" /> He developed a mathematical theory for elucidating these bifurcations and his studies are known to be in use in various applications.<ref name="Soumitro Banerjee on IISER" /> He has also worked extensively on nonlinear phenomena in power electronics. He has documented his researches by way of several articles;<ref name="Browse by Fellow">{{Cite web |url=http://repository.ias.ac.in/view/fellows/Banerjee=3ASoumitro=3A=3A.html |title=Browse by Fellow |date=2016 |publisher=Indian Academy of Sciences}}</ref>{{Refn|group=note|Please see ''Articles'' section}} Google Scholar and ResearchGate, online article repositories of scientific articles, have listed many of them.<ref name="On Google Scholar">{{Cite web |url=https://scholar.google.co.in/citations?user=8R_8gjYAAAAJ&hl=en |title=On Google Scholar |date=2016 |publisher=Google Scholar}}</ref><ref name="On ResearchGate">{{Cite web |url=https://www.researchgate.net/researcher/13561682_Soumitro_Banerjee |title=On ResearchGate |date=2016 |publisher=On ResearchGate}}</ref> Besides, he has made several presentations<ref name="Border Collision and Bifurcation: Theory and Applications">{{Cite web |url=http://iwcsn2006.irmacs.sfu.ca/pdf/soumitro.banerjee.pdf |title=Border Collision and Bifurcation: Theory and Applications |last=Soumitro Banerjee |date=2017 |publisher=International Workshop on Complex Systems and Networks 2006}}</ref><ref name="Qualitative Change in Dynamical Status Theory and Open Problems">{{Cite web |url=http://www.ias.ac.in/public/Resources/Events/Mid_Year_Meetings/17_soumitrobanerjee.pdf |title=Qualitative Change in Dynamical Status Theory and Open Problems |last=Soumitro Banerjee |date=2017 |publisher=Indian Academy of Sciences}}</ref> and has authored two books, ''Dynamics for Engineers'', which details modelling and analysis of [[dynamical systems]],<ref name="Dynamics for Engineers">{{Cite book |url=http://eu.wiley.com/WileyCDA/WileyTitle/productCd-0470868430.html |title=Dynamics for Engineers |last=Soumitro Banerjee |publisher=Wiley |isbn=978-0-470-86843-0 |publication-date=June 2005 |page=294 |language=English}}</ref> and ''Wind Electrical Systems'', the first Indian book on [[wind energy]] conversion.<ref name="BhadraKastha2005">{{cite book|author1=S. N. Bhadra|author2=D. Kastha|author3=Soumitro Banerjee|title=Wind Electrical Systems|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=vt4eAQAAIAAJ|date=17 November 2005|publisher=OUP India|isbn=978-0-19-567093-6}}</ref> He has also edited a book, ''Nonlinear Phenomena in Power Electronics: Bifurcations, Chaos, Control, and Applications'',<ref name="BanerjeeVerghese2001">{{cite book|author1=Soumitro Banerjee|author2=George C. Verghese|title=Nonlinear Phenomena in Power Electronics: Bifurcations, Chaos, Control, and Applications|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wnYeAQAAIAAJ|date=16 July 2001|publisher=Wiley|isbn=978-0-7803-5383-1}}</ref> in which he has written a number of chapters.<ref name="Nonlinear Phenomena in Power Electronics: Bifurcations, Chaos, Control, and Applications">{{Cite web |url=http://eu.wiley.com/WileyCDA/WileyTitle/productCd-0780353838,miniSiteCd-IEEE2.html |title=Nonlinear Phenomena in Power Electronics: Bifurcations, Chaos, Control, and Applications |date=2017 |publisher=Wiley}}</ref>

Banerjee was associated with three journals of the [[Institute of Electrical and Electronic Engineers]]; he served as the associate editor of IEEE Transactions on Circuits and Systems II (2003–05) and of the IEEE Transactions on Circuits and Systems (2006–07) and is the associate editor of IEEE Circuits & Systems Society Newsletter since 2010.<ref name="Indian fellow" /> His efforts have been reported in the initiation of the ''National Conference on Nonlinear Systems and Dynamics'' (NCNSD) and he served as the convenor of the inaugural conference held at IIT Kharagpur campus in December 2003.<ref name="Preface NCNSD">{{Cite web |url=http://www.ncnsd.org/proceedings/proceeding03/html/pdf/preface.pdf |title=Preface NCNSD |date=2017 |publisher=National Conference on Nonlinear Systems and Dynamics}}</ref> he has also presented a number of papers at various editions of the conference.<ref name="Nonlinear Phenomena in Engineering and Social Sciences">{{Cite web |url=http://www.ncnsd.org/proceedings/proceeding06/NPES.php |title=Nonlinear Phenomena in Engineering and Social Sciences |date=2017 |publisher=NCNSD-2006}}</ref><ref name="Bifurcation Theory">{{Cite web |url=http://www.ncnsd.org/proceedings/proceeding06/BT.php |title=Bifurcation Theory |date=2017 |publisher=NCNSD-2006}}</ref><ref name="Dynamics of a mass on moving belt with dry friction">{{Cite web |url=http://www.ncnsd.org/proceedings/proceeding05/bt.php |title=Dynamics of a mass on moving belt with dry friction |date=2017 |publisher=NCNSD-2005}}</ref> He is the general secretary of ''Breakthrough Science Society'', a non-governmental organization for the popularization of science and sits in the editorial board of its journal.<ref name="All India Committee">{{Cite web |url=http://www.breakthrough-india.org/nec.html |title=All India Committee |date=2017 |publisher=Breakthrough Science Society}}</ref> He is also the editor of ''Prakriti'', a [[Bengali language]] science magazine.<ref name="Soumitro Banerjee on IISER" /> He has sat in the Sectional Committees on Electrical Engineering of such science academies as Indian National Academy of Engineering (2005–07 and 2013–15), Indian National Science Academy (2012–14) and Indian Academy of Sciences (2010–12.<ref name="Profile on TWAS" /> He has also been associated with several government agencies which included the Engineering Sciences Research Committee of the Council of Scientific and Industrial Research, Programme Advisory Committee in Electrical, Electronic and Computer Engineering of the [[Department of Science and Technology (India)|Department of Science and Technology]] (DST) as well as the Board of Members of West Bengal Renewable Energy Development Agency (WBREDA) and he is a member of the Screening Committee on Engineering for ''Inspire Faculty Award'' of the DST.<ref name="Inspire Faculty Award">{{Cite web |url=http://www.inspire-dst.gov.in/List_of_Chairpersons_Members.pdf |title=Inspire Faculty Award |date=2017 |publisher=Department of Science and Technology}}</ref>

== Awards and honors ==
Banerjee received the Boyscast Fellowship of the Department of Science and Technology in 1996 which enabled him to carry out collaborative research at the [[University of Maryland]].<ref name="Faculty profile" /> The [[Council of Scientific and Industrial Research]] awarded him the [[Shanti Swarup Bhatnagar Prize]], one of the highest Indian science awards in 2003.<ref name="Engineering Sciences">{{Cite web |url=http://www.csir.res.in/external/heads/career/award/BPRIZE/Engineering_SCIENCES.htm |title=Engineering Sciences |date=2016 |publisher=Council of Scientific and Industrial Research |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923211647/http://www.csir.res.in/external/heads/career/award/BPRIZE/Engineering_SCIENCES.htm |archivedate=2015-09-23 |df= }}</ref> The next year, [[Thomson Scientific]] included him in the list of top 250 scientists in the world with the highest citation count<ref name="Research Day and Citation Laureate India 2004 Awards">{{Cite web |url=http://ncsi.iisc.ernet.in/pipermail/lis-forum/2004-October/001318.html |title=Research Day and Citation Laureate India 2004 Awards |date=October 8, 2004 |publisher=Indian Institute of Science}}</ref> in the Engineering category and awarded him the 2004 Citation Laureate Award.<ref name="Thomson Citation Laureate award for 7 scientists ">{{Cite web |url=http://archive.deccanherald.com/deccanherald/oct112004/c10.asp |title=Thomson Citation Laureate award for 7 scientists |date=October 11, 2004 |publisher=Deccan Herald |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202035508/http://archive.deccanherald.com/deccanherald/oct112004/c10.asp |archivedate=February 2, 2017 |df= }}</ref> The same year, the Indian National Academy of Engineering elected him as a fellow<ref name="Banerjee on INAE">{{Cite web |url=https://inae.in/expert-search/index.php/soumitro-banerjee |title=Banerjee on INAE |date=2017 |publisher=Indian National Academy of Engineering }}{{dead link|date=May 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> and he became a fellow of the Indian Academy of Sciences <ref name="Fellow profile" /> and the Indian National Science Academy in 2005 and 2007 respectively.<ref name="INSA Year Book 2016">{{Cite web |url=http://www.insaindia.res.in/pdf/YearBook_2016.pdf |title=INSA Year Book 2016 |date=2016 |publisher=Indian National Science Academy}}</ref> He featured in the 2011 fellowship list of the West Bengal Academy of Science and Technology and the elected fellowship of [[The World Academy of Sciences]] reached him in 2012,<ref name="TWAS fellow" /> followed by fellowships of the [[Institute of Electrical and Electronic Engineers]] in 2013<ref name="IEEE Fellows Directory" /> and the National Academy of Sciences, India in 2014.<ref name="NASI Year Book 2015">{{Cite web |url=http://www.nasi.org.in/Year%20Book%202015.pdf |title=NASI Year Book 2015 |date=2016 |publisher=National Academy of Sciences, India}}</ref> The Department of Science and Technology selected him for the J. C. Bose National fellowship in 2015.<ref name="Faculty profile" />

